  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Bancamia Bond</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">IFCs proposed project consists of a bond investment of up to COP100,000 million in Bancamia (the Bank) to support the growth of the Banks microenterprise loan portfolio in rural areas of Colombia. Bancamia started operating as a bank in 2008 and is currently Colombias largest private microfinance institution.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The proposed investment is expected to have the following development impact: (i)	Increase banking penetration and access to financial services to underserved microenterprises in Colombia; (ii)	Increase employment generation, since micro and small enterprises are the main drivers of employment;  (iii)	Increase the access to finance to underserved women micro-entrepreneurs;  (iv)	Expand the availability of financial services in the rural areas of Colombia; and (v)	Deepen financial and capital markets in Colombia.</narrative>
  </description>
